description:
About Spaceman Jax, Through the Mantagon Minefield:

Curio & Co. has released another jewel from the past: the first issue of Spaceman Jax comics to tie in with the 1960s animated TV show, Spaceman Jax and the Galactic Adventures. Dont worry if you dont remember it. The show, like the comics, never existed.

The project is another imaginary trip down memory lane from Curio & Co. Since 2010, Curio & Co. has been creating entertainment collectibles from an alternate history pop culture properties that never existed in order to play with the power of nostalgia to re-create warm memories from childhood. Who couldnt use more of that, right?

This comic, Spaceman Jax Through the Mantagon Minefield, recreates the Silver Age comics of the 1960s. It includes fictional vintage ads that provide a commentary on the time period while providing a delightful contrast to the commercialism of today. Spaceman Jax Through the Mantagon Minefield even recreates some of the technical restrictions in the way comics were printed in the past to capture the warmth and the charm of the analog world.

Most importantly, this comic, like all of Curio & Co.s products, offer a chance to re-live childhood memories. These were the kind of comics that you hid behind the textbook in Mrs. Hendersons Social Studies class. Shed always threaten to take it away if she saw it again, but she never did. (She was sweeter than we ever gave her credit for.)

So take a stroll back to the easier days of childhood with Spaceman Jax Through the Mantagon Minefield. Maybe even bring it to the office and sneak a peak at work to reassure yourself that some things never change.
name: Spaceman Jax

deck: Mnemonic Kid was a rejected Legionnaire applicant, who could induce memory loss.
description:
History

Mnemonic Kid was a rejected Legionnaire applicant, who could induce memory loss.

Angry that she had been rejected, she plotted her revenge by wiping parts of the Legionnaire's memories. Another Legion reject, Fortress Lad, came to the rescue by transforming into a giant fortress in order to protect the Legionnaires.

Mnemonic Kid continued to use her powers against Fortress Lad, who resisted at the cost of losing all of his memories. As a last resort, Mnemonic Kid threw a grenade at Fortress Lad (and the Legionnaires inside him), but she caught the impact of the explosion herself and died.

Powers and Abilities

Mnemonic Kid had the power to induce memory loss, but could not return it once it was taken away.

deck:
Despite this Russian composer's "Contemporary Era" lifetime, most of his brilliant works were styled romantic.
(1873-1943)
description:
Rachmaninoff was born on April Fools 1873 to a Russian-Moldavian family.

By the age of 18 he was an excellent pianist. Two years later, he wrote an opera that was given the Moscow Conservatory's Great Gold Medal, the third person to receive that honor.

Later in his life he wrote many other works that have come to be respected as the works of a genius.

He died in his Beverly Hills home on March 28,1943.
name: Sergei Rachmaninoff

deck: Resident of Earth-16, girlfriend of Damian Wayne and daughter of Lex Luthor.
description:
The daughter of supervillain Lex Luthor, Alexis Luthor lives in the peaceful yet boring earth-16, where all the troubles of the world have been resolved thanks to superheroes and where the sons and daughters of superheros and supervillians alike live peacefully.

Despite this, Alexis lives ostracized because of her linage. Even though she is in a secret relationship with Damian Wayne, she is not always invited to important events such as Sister Miracle's party due to her father having killed Superman.

Alexis was the vehicle used by the Gentry to wreck havoc on the super robots software to send them into a rampage. Whether she was stopped and whether she is still in a relationship with Damian Wayne is unknown.

Alexis was created by Grant Morrison and Ben Oliver. As with Damian Wayne and Christopher Kent, she was based on Ardora, a character of the Super Sons saga.
name: Alexis Luthor

description:
Origin

As a boy Peter Bold was shipwrecked on a mysterious island with a group of his schoolmates. After coming up with an idea to drive away a pack of rats he was derisively nicknamed "The Swamp Rat"

Unfortunately the island was also inhabited by a lost tribe of Mayas who attacked the group on first contact. Peter defended his friends and managed to fight off and defeat one of the tribe's warriors, which gained him some respect with the tribesmen.

Fortunately the Mayas had a longstanding prophecy about a legendary white god, and believed Peter to be the fulfillment of this prophecy. To protect the other kids Peter decided to play along with this idea and took part in a number of trials, each time he succeeded in a trial the Mayas gave him a tattoo.

On the island Pete was befriended by a Mongoose which he named Mong.
name: The Swamp Rat

deck: After his defeat in the Second Punic War against Scipio Africanus, Carthaginian general Hannibal Barca retreated south, desperate to find a way to combat the Roman Republic. He found this way in bathing in the Rhynin-influenced River of Youth, and became an immortal Shaytan. Hannibal vowed to never let what had occurred to his civilization to happen again, and has since become the leader of the fight against evil in this world. He currently acts as head of the Phantom Squad.
